OL,3,CMobile phones to be banned across
OL,4,Cschools in England under new plans
OL,6,FBans on smartphones in schools could
OL,7,Fsoon become law across England, as the
OL,8,Fgovernment seeks to make its guidance
OL,9,Fstatutory.
OL,11,FAn amendment is set to be introduced
OL,12,Fto the Children's Wellbeing and
OL,13,FSchools Bill in the House of Lords, a
OL,14,FDepartment for Education (DfE)
OL,15,Fspokesperson said on Monday.
OL,17,F"We have been consistently clear that
OL,18,Fmobile phones have no place in
OL,19,Fschools, and the majority already
OL,20,Fprohibit them," the spokesperson said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776764340
OL,3,CMobile phones to be banned across
OL,4,Cschools in England under new plans
OL,6,F"This amendment makes existing
OL,7,Fguidance statutory, giving legal force
OL,8,Fto what schools are already doing in
OL,9,Fpractice.
OL,11,F"It builds on the steps we've already
OL,12,Ftaken to strengthen enforcement, with
OL,13,FOfsted considering schools' mobile
OL,14,Fphone policies as part of inspection
OL,15,Ffrom this month.
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,26,@sD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776764340
OL,3,CMobile phones to be banned across
OL,4,Cschools in England under new plans
OL,6,F"We will always put children's
OL,7,Finterests first, including through
OL,8,Fthis Bill - which is widely recognised
OL,9,Fas the biggest piece of child
OL,10,Fsafeguarding legislation in decades,
OL,11,Fwith critical measures like laws to
OL,12,Fcrack down on profiteering in
OL,13,Fchildren's social care and a new
OL,14,Funique identifier to stop children
OL,15,Ffalling through the cracks."
OL,17,FMPs are understood to be voting on the
OL,18,FGovernment amendment on Wednesday.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
