CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776764340
OL,3,CMobile phones to be banned across
OL,4,Cschools in England under new plans
OL,6,FOn Monday, peers voted through a
OL,7,FConservative amendment to the Bill on
OL,8,Fmobile phones, voting 276 to 169 to
OL,9,Fban pupils from having smartphones
OL,10,Fduring the school day.
OL,12,FThe proposal includes potential
OL,13,Fexemptions for sixth formers, medical
OL,14,Fdevices and some boarding school
OL,15,Fsettings, and faces further scrutiny
OL,16,Fin the House of Commons, which has
OL,17,Fpreviously rejected it.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776764340
OL,3,CMobile phones to be banned across
OL,4,Cschools in England under new plans
OL,6,FThe Education Secretary has previously
OL,7,Fwritten to headteachers in England to
OL,8,Fstress that schools should be phone-
OL,9,Ffree throughout the school day, but
OL,10,Fthe guidance has been non-statutory.
OL,12,FThe headteachers' union, NAHT,
OL,13,Fpreviously expressed support for
OL,14,Fmaking the ban a law.
OL,16,F"Statutory guidance will give school
OL,17,Fleaders the clarity they need to
OL,18,Fimplement a ban, and will remove any
OL,19,Fambiguity or differences between how
OL,20,Fschools approach smartphone policies,"
OL,21,Fgeneral secretary Paul Whiteman said.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776764340
OL,3,CMobile phones to be banned across
OL,4,Cschools in England under new plans
OL,6,F"Schools will only then need to decide
OL,7,Fhow to implement and enforce a ban
OL,8,Facross their school community, and the
OL,9,FGovernment must provide any support
OL,10,Fthey require to do so effectively.
OL,12,F"Some schools will need time to
OL,13,Fcommunicate with parents and pupils on
OL,14,Fthe implementation of a complete ban
OL,15,Fwhere this is not already in place."
OL,17,FShadow education minister Baroness
OL,18,FBarran told the Lords the current
OL,19,Fguidance "still allows schools to have
OL,20,Fa so-called 'not seen, not heard'
OL,21,Fpolicy".
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUwD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1776764340
OL,3,CMobile phones to be banned across
OL,4,Cschools in England under new plans
OL,6,F"There is so much evidence that the
OL,7,Fpresence of a smartphone in one's bag
OL,8,For pocket is a distraction, that the
OL,9,Ftemptation to turn it on when going to
OL,10,Fthe lavatory, when out of sight, when
OL,11,Fin the playground, is almost
OL,12,Firresistible. Indeed, it happens to
OL,13,Fadults too," she said.
OL,15,F"So, given that that is the case,
OL,16,Fputting flawed guidance on a statutory
OL,17,Ffooting achieves nothing."
OL,26,@wD@AOUyD@ZO]
